Introduction to SQL

Welcome to the Introduction to SQL Workshop on GitHub! This comprehensive course is designed to provide you with a solid foundation in Structured Query Language (SQL) and empower you to interact with databases proficiently.

Here's a breakdown of what you can expect to learn:

Foundations of SQL Querying
Mastering basic SQL syntax
Retrieving data from databases effectively
Data Aggregation and Grouping
Understanding how to summarize and group data
Performing aggregate functions for analysis
Core Database Concepts
Exploring key terminology and principles of databases
Database Modeling
Designing database schemas for efficient data storage
Implementing normalization techniques for data integrity
Understanding Joins
Utilizing joins to combine data from multiple tables
Mastering different types of joins for complex queries
Views, Subqueries, and Indexes
Creating and managing views for data abstraction
Harnessing the power of subqueries for advanced querying
Optimizing query performance with indexes
Throughout the Section, you'll engage in practical exercises and real-world examples to reinforce your understanding of SQL concepts. By the end of this workshop, you'll be equipped with the skills to navigate SQL databases confidently and effectively manage data. Let's embark on this journey into the world of SQL together!
